    public override async Task SeedAsync()
    {
        // ── Overview (Article) ───────────────────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Announcements Admin",
            Slug = "announcements-admin-overview",
            Summary = "How admins and managers send company announcements: the Admin > Announcements panel, sending a new announcement (severity, scope, acknowledgment, expiry), the sent-announcements list and acknowledgment roster, and reusable templates.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 6,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 1,
            AppRoutes = """["/admin/announcements"]""",
            Tags = """["announcements","admin","communication","broadcast"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Announcements Admin\n\nAnnouncements are official messages that admins and managers broadcast to the company. Unlike a chat message, an announcement is targeted and trackable: you choose who sees it, how urgent it is, whether people must acknowledge it, and when it expires. Recipients see it as an overlay banner the moment it is sent (delivered in real time), and you can check exactly who has acknowledged it.\n\nThis admin panel is the single place to **send** announcements, **review** everything that has been sent, see **who acknowledged** each one, and manage reusable **templates**. (Announcement authoring used to be framed as living inside Chat — it does not. The Chat broadcast channel surfaces announcements, but you compose and manage them here, in Admin.)\n\n### Finding the panel\n\nGo to **Admin → Announcements** (route `/admin/announcements`). The panel has two tabs:\n\n- **Announcements** — the list of everything sent, with its New Announcement button.\n- **Templates** — reusable announcement presets, with its New Template button.\n\nThe panel is restricted by role: sending announcements and viewing the sent list / acknowledgments requires **Admin or Manager**; creating and deleting **templates** requires **Admin**.\n\n### Sending a new announcement\n\nFrom the **Announcements** tab, click **New Announcement** (the campaign icon) to open the Send Announcement dialog. Fill in:\n\n- **Template** (optional) — pick a saved template to prefill the content, severity, scope, and acknowledgment toggle. You can then edit any field before sending.\n- **Title** (required, up to 200 characters) — the headline recipients see.\n- **Content** (required, up to 5,000 characters) — the body of the message.\n- **Severity** (required) — **Info**, **Warning**, or **Critical**. Severity colors the chip and signals urgency.\n- **Scope** (required) — who receives it (see below).\n- **Target Teams** — appears only for the team-based scopes; pick one or more teams.\n- **Expires At** (optional) — a date after which the announcement stops surfacing. Leave blank for no expiry.\n- **Require Acknowledgment** (toggle) — when on, recipients must click to acknowledge, and you can track who has.\n\nClick **Send**. The announcement is delivered immediately to its audience and appears at the top of the sent list.\n\n### Scope — who receives it\n\nScope controls the audience:\n\n- **Company-Wide** — everyone in the company.\n- **Selected Teams** — members of one or more teams you pick in Target Teams.\n- **Individual Team** — a single team you pick in Target Teams.\n- **Team Leads Only** — only the leads of the target teams, not every member.\n\nFor any of the team-based scopes, the **Target Teams** multi-select appears so you can choose which teams the announcement targets.\n\n### The sent-announcements list\n\nThe **Announcements** tab lists everything sent, newest first. Columns include the **Title**, a colored **Severity** chip, the **Scope**, **Sent By** (who created it), **Sent** (date and time), and **Acks** — the count of people who have acknowledged it. New announcements appear at the top in real time, even ones sent by a colleague while you are looking at the list.\n\n### The acknowledgment roster\n\nClick any row (or the visibility / eye icon on it) to open the **Acknowledgments** dialog. It shows a header count of how many people have acknowledged, a note if acknowledgment was required, and a list of each person who acknowledged with the date and time they did. If the announcement did not require acknowledgment, the roster simply reflects anyone who chose to acknowledge. This is how you confirm a critical notice actually reached the people who needed to see it.\n\n### Templates\n\nFrequently-repeated announcements (a monthly safety reminder, a maintenance-window notice) are worth saving as **templates**. Switch to the **Templates** tab and click **New Template** to create one with:\n\n- **Name** (required) — how the template shows up in the picker.\n- **Content** (required) — the default body text.\n- **Default Severity** and **Default Scope** — the values prefilled when the template is chosen.\n- **Require Acknowledgment by Default** — whether the acknowledgment toggle starts on.\n\nSaved templates appear in the Templates list and in the **Template** dropdown of the Send Announcement dialog. To remove one, click the **delete** icon on its row and confirm — deletion is permanent, but it does not affect announcements already sent from it.\n\n### Severity, acknowledgment, and expiry at a glance\n\n- **Severity** is purely a signal of urgency and what color the chip is — it does not change the audience.\n- **Require Acknowledgment** is what makes the Acks count and the roster meaningful — without it, people simply read the banner.\n- **Expires At** stops the announcement from surfacing after the date; it does not delete the record, so it still appears in the sent list and its roster stays available.","sections":[]}"""
